\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Could I have your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 W. Thorn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What's your address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well, my a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 ddress at the moment is {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address
}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}42 St E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 van's Road, North{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} Kensington. I've lived there forty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Can you remember what year you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Paddington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was this in a house or a hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 In - in - in - in - in - in the slums. By - Cirencester Street, the well known slums. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How long did you live there for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh - we had so many addresses, we couldn't - couldn't pay the rent, we had to keep moving. And we come home from - come home from school and - 
find - find your - find your bits and pieces slung out on the road, or passed over - or passed over the wall to the - the next bloke to look after and while you're - the landlord come in - in he found nothing there. And you was in - in the next garden see
. He looked after 'em until we found - found a place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you often have to keep moving like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes, you - you got slung out if you owed - we - we only - we only paid four and six a week rent - for - for - for - for - for two rooms, in the 
basement. But it was all like that in them days. And if - if - if you couldn't find your - your four and six pence you was out the next week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where would you go to from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh you - you could go to - you'd either had to go in the work house o
r you'd have to - to - you'd sleep in the - sleep in - in the - in a street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How would you find another place to live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - my mother found it for us. She'd go - she'd go to work all day and - come home and go house hunting of a night and - r
oom hunting, as long as you found a place to live in, if it was only for two or three nights it was all right. My - my wife, she - she had the same thing, her - her - her - her people, they had - they had - they had - they had a laundry and they - they ha
d
 - they had - owed a - month's rent and the - the landlord come on them to - and pinched the house with the furniture for a month's rent. See? They - they were the - that was the - the Rider's in - in Ladbroke Grove - they - they're very fine people they 
are, Riders - don't - don't do - don't do no dealings with them, I wouldn't buy a house off of them or nothing off of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 These families were pretty rotten were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh Rack - Rackman wasn't in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would they call around all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh they - they - they'd be waiting on the doorstep if - if - if - me old - old - old man would go out looking for a job, come home and be out there all day, come home looking for a job and then - and - and then they'd find the landlord waiting on the do
orstep for him. When you going to pay me? As if -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were all the landlords the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh Lor', yes, in them - in them - in them areas. Don't know round - round - round - about about - Paddington and - Clarendon Street and Cirencester Street and - S
eany Street and Alfreds Road and all those, terrible places. You had no bathrooms or - you only - had the - the only toilet you had was out - out in the - in the yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How many rooms would you have in these houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh what - only two, we only had two rooms downstairs in the basement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How many were there of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Ten of us. Yes, we - we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It must have been very cramped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Cramped, I should - I mean you sleep - you see you slept as - you slept eight kids in the bed and the - the 
old - me old man and the old lady slept in the - in - in the kitchen. Where you done - did - did - done - done the washing and the cooking and the - everything in the - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So you only had the kitchen and a bedroom really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, that's all. And
 the lavatory was out - out - out in the scullery, I mean, in the - out in the - upstairs there was three rooms on the ground floor. Two rooms on the next floor and three rooms on the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 But they were different families in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, all diffe
rent families, oh yes. But you just - it's the - it's the same letting - it's the same letting now as what it - it is - it's the same conditions now as what - it is with the coloured people now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Too many people in one small space?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 In the - where the - the house I'm living in now - next door - they've got nineteen people living in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They've got to to survive really haven't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They've got to live - well they shouldn't be here should they. That's the point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did the landlord ever bring the police in and things like that when you were living in these houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes, the police was - they - they - the police, it was nothing for them to come in and - and - and - and - and settle a squabble. And - and - and when I - when 
I was eleven and I left school - on the Friday, I got a job at the - at - at - at the pawn shop. Sleep in. Four shillings a week and sleep in under the counter - in the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was this in Paddington?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 In here, yes. Mela - Melachies - pawn shop. Opposite the Ben Johnson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Fourteen. And I stuck - stuck that a year, and when I asked him for a rise he said, yes, you can have a rise, sixpence. Sixpence a week rise. I told him what he can do with his sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he provide food and things like that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh food, yes, yes. But you - you had to sleep under the counter. The only thing there - the only thing was see - I was - I was the best - best - best - best - my - my mate and I - we - we were the best 
- best - two best - best dressed boys in the - in - in - in the neighbourhood because - when we went out of a night we - we - we borrowed a suit that some - somebody had pawned. And wrapped it up and had a - had another - had another colour the next night
. So nobody wouldn't recognise their - their suit if they see us in it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How did you get on for clothes when you were living in Cirencester Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh we just pulled 'em on. Pulled - pulled 'em - some tuppenny pair of boots on and tuppence on the b
arrow, odd - odd boots. And odd - odd socks. I sung in a church choir. And the - the - in - in - Holy Trinity church choir, Bishops Road, it was a very very very very - rich church. And I got four pound fifteen a quarter for singing in the church choir. A
nd I got slung out because I hadn't got no clothes to - to - of course they - they - they all wore Eton suits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Wouldn't they provide you with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, they wouldn't - they - they - they - they - they might - they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you wear cassocks and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
They - they - and - what was I going to say now. No, they slung - slung me out of - they - they - 'cos I - I hadn't got Eton suit, and - I was chosen to go to Paris to sing - sing in - sing in the church choir there, going for the 
London schoolboys. And I - I - I was only thirteen. And because I hadn't got an Eton suit to go in - I couldn't go and - and one - one of the boys called the - called me ragged - ragged arse so I punched him on the nose and I got the sack out the choir. H
e had all the blood all down - down his surplice and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did your mother or father ever make or men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298  clothes for your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh, they - they can - they done the best they could you know, patch - patched 'em up. But what can you - what can you do w
ith a - patch - patching up old - old clothes that somebody else has had the used of - for years. Perhaps been handed down from - well one - one - one - one - one - hands only, one down to - down to the other until it got too small for them and then - the
y - they slung it in the rag bag and the rag shop bought 'em and they sold 'em tuppence on - on the railings, down the rag fair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you ever buy the clothes new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no. Never new - never no new - never knew what a new suit was. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How many times do you think you had to change house before 1918?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
19 - 1918? Wait a minute, I'm just trying to think. I should say fifteen times. Because we couldn't pay the rent, couldn't - couldn't pay the rent. See, the old man was - was a - was
 a time serving soldier. Well when he come out the Army - 'course time serving soldiers - in them day, they - they - they hadn't got no trade. See - he couldn't get a job and - he - he - if he got a job, if he got a job - he was in the Artillery - got - h
e got a job as a - as a car}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
man. Temporary job. I mean and - and - unless you was a - unless you was a brickie - a bricklayer or a carpenter or something like that or - and - you went labouring for three and a tanner a day or - or four bob a day, you know, 
dig - digging the roads, they - they - they - didn't - the Borough used - used to pay - used to pay you every night then, see, and then if they didn't want you the next day they - they - they - it was no skin off their nose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever have any help from the Parish at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. In - we went to the poor law school. Oh yes, I went to the poor law school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 That - that - that - that was - the - you go in there when the old man was out of work and had no grub. You - you -
 you go - go to the - go to the Relieving Officer. Old Stevens. The Relieving Officer in Woodfield Road, he was a nice bastard he was. And he'd say, all right, well we'll - go - go - go with - he'd give you - give you - give you a ticket for some - for so
m
e bread and margarine and that. Well bring 'em in Monday. Well the old - the old man had to cart - cart you - cart you in, you'd stop - you'd stop away until - until - until - until you - you - and - and - until he found a job of some sort. And as soon as
 he found a job he'd come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was he very often out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 YES? HE - he was out of work - he was out of work two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 years right off and - then eighteen months and then he'd do - do - do three months work, then he'd do - do - do's do a bit of roa
d digging. He - he - he - the only job he - the only job he had - I - I remember - the longest job he had was from about 1912 'til - to 1914. He had a job as a carman. Fairhold's carman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was that driving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Driving a - a - pair - pair - pair of horse, for a - for a - for a br}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 w - brew - for a brewery. And - and he - he - then the war broke out and he - he got - he got called up again, that's when things began to change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 He got paid during that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 He - well he got paid - he got paid then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would all of you go into the poor law school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, only - only those - only - only those as - was - was old enough to - to - to - to work for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So you'd have to work when you went in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, yes, yes, you had to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It wasn't like a school in the sense of lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
You had to do so many - so many - so much lessons - but you had to do - you had to scrub the rooms and bedrooms and the - the dayroom and the dining room and - and the floor and all that and - all the - t
he yards and the lavatories, you had to clean - see, then - then - then these poor law schools, there's - that is - two - three - two hundred and fifty boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Only single sex?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, see the boys and of course the girls went a different place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was this the only school you ever went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, I went to - I went to - I went to St Paul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 s school in Harrow Road, in - in - Waverley Road. Oh they - they - old - old Hennett the schoolmaster, he was a decent old sort, he - he always - he always used
 to call - call his boys - get - put your hands up those who ain't had no breakfast, then he'd send some out - he'd send out and buy - buy - buy - buy - buy a big - big - a - a - a big paper full of - of rolls. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Out of his own pocket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. And say, and don't sling the paper on the playground. Else you won't you get any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When did you go to that school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh when we - when I was old enough to go to school. When - when I - when I was about four - about three and a half to four years old.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When did you go to the poor law school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh that - that - when - well when - when - when - when the old man was out of work you simply left - say St Paul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 s school and carried on when you come out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So you kept chopping and changing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Changing, that's it. Chopping and changing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Which of the two did you prefer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh St - St Paul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 s school of course. I mean you - you was free in the evenings. You was never free in the evenings in - in the poor law schools. You knew 
you only had to - you only had porridge and bread and margarine for breakfast. And sup - suet - suet pudding and dumplings and that for dinner you know, you - never had no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was this actually part of the work house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It was - was - was the work house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It was all boys rather than adults as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
That was all boys, I'm talking about boys, they never take - they never - never - after you was four - fifteen - and a half, if you - if you was fit you went in the Navy. Yes, in the boys service, in the boys service. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where would adults be, didn't they have adult work houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No, no, no, they - they - oh they had adult - adult work house, they - they - they they had a - places all over London for adults, I mean they had to chop - tey had to chop wood and all kinds of things. And - to - to earn their keep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did your father ever have to go in to one of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, he never went into one of them, he - he kept out - he kept out of that. He - 'cos he was a - I'll give him his du
e, he was always look - look - looking for work, but he never found it, he - he used to come home - he used to come home - come home tired out. Then he'd go out at six o'clock and seven o'clock in the morning, walk all over London - London to find a job a
nd he might find a week's work. Find it down Covent Garden. Find a week's work then find - at a hotel he'd find a week's work somewhere so - somebody'd be away sick. A - a porter or somebody like that you see. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What would your mother do, would she work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes? Well my mother she worked at - she - she had a good - she had a good job. What I say was a good job. She - she worked for Madame Tussauds. She was cook - for Madame Tussauds restaurant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Is that in Baker Street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Baker Street. A
nd it used to be my job every night - at eight o'clock, to walk from Paddington, Harrow Road down - down - down to Baker Street, with a bag - shopping bag, and a bit of str}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 
ing, and a - and a butchers hoo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 k and - she - she - she used to let the the butchers 
hook down and pull the bag up and send it down full of grub for - for - for the - for the next day's dinner. You see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How many hours a day did she work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 She - she - she worked - she worked - she - she worked there from about - half past seven in the morning 'til eleven o'clock at night.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would she have to walk there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
She - she - she got a - got a - she got a penny - the penny bus. What they call the old - the old blue buses, the old horse buses. And they used to - used to run - used to run from - Queen's Park - to Great Portland Street. Penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When you weren't at the poor law school and your mother was out working who would do the cooking in your house, how would you eat?
