 you get the coal from? So I showed him. Oh he said, in - in - in - in this bag - there's a big lump - lump of coal at the bottom for the fire. See? So he - he marched me a little way back to - to - to - to to Alsop Place at Baker Street and that's where 
t
he kitchen was up the top. And - and - and - and - I whistled up and she - she looked down, she said, what do you want? I said to her, the copper - the copper's nicked me. She said, what the bloody hell does he want. I said, I - I suppose he wants some su
pper. So she came down, she - she brought him down - brought him down a packet - a packet of sand wi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
ches and a - and a jug of cocoa. And then - while he was getting that down him, I - I nipped it.
