\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 1959. And I've never been ill before. With all that 
rough - rough childhood and I never - never - never - my - my old man, he died - he died in 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he get hurt in the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well he got - he got - he got - he got a kick in - and that in the throat by a German prison - prisoner, and of course 
caused the cancer. He only - he only lived a few months with it. And my - my mother died - eighteen months afterwards. So then I had to go - go - go - we all went in different ways in - in lodgings you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say you had ten brothers and sisters? How many brothers did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
I had four - six - I had six brothers and four - four - four - six - six - six brothers and two - and two sisters. And then mum and dad. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How much older or younger were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I was - I was the second eldest. The eldest he - he went in the Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How much older than you was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Eleven months. We all about eleven months between us. They used to send us to Sunday - Sunday school on a Sunday, so they could get on the bed and - and - and enjoy themselve
s. I mean, I'm - I'm telling you as - as - as - as it was. And then - not mincing matters. And I - then - 1921 - when the coal strike came on, we - we - we - we got a - we got put off at Debenham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 s, for - for - for - for three months. We was - we was paid 
ten shillings a week retaining fee. We wasn't sacked. They paid us ten shillings a week retaining fee - and we - we - we had to - to go - to - to - to go to the Labour - Labour Exchange three times a week and draw the Labour Exchange money on top of their
 - to the ten shillings they allow us and then when the jobs come along, they took us back you see. Well - I - I got a barrow, I went down Smithfield market, and then I bought a load of rabbits. I give - give nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pence each for these rabbits and - and set 
up - set up a - set up - set up - a stall in Harrow Road. I didn't know nothing about rabbits. I couldn't bloody well skin one. The woman, she said, how much are rabbits? I said, one and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pence each. I got tanner - I got a - a tanner - a tanner on a r
abbit was a lot of money them days, so she said, well will you skin it for me? I said, oh yes, I'll skin if for you. So I say I skinned it - I chopped it's legs off and it's head off and then wrapped it up I said, is that your dog? That your dog fighting 
up the road missus? She said, yes, I believe it is. While she's looking up the road I wrapped her - wrapped it up and give - give it to her and took her one and - one and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pence and - and that was it. And then - then - then I can't - then when a copper
 with a food inspector, at the end of the day and - and told me I'd got to sling 'em all away 'cos they were rotten. They'd got the maggots in 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you have meat very often when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, we used to get it - used to get up i
n the morning very early. About half past five or six and go - go down to the butchers in - in - in Bishops - Bishops Road and - go to Whiteley's and - and get two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298  two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pennorth of stale meat. Two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9516132\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pennorth of stale bread, you get - you get four loaves for tuppence. Four full loaves for tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would this all come out of your mother's money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How much did she get a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 She used to get eighteen - eighteen shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Which was quite a lot really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It was quite a 
lot, well a lot of hours too. Oh, about half past seven in the morning 'til eleven at night. It was two weeks work in one. Then she - then she - she'd - she'd - she'd come home and do the work - after she come home she'd do - do - do - do - do - do - do t
he washing. After been doing - doing - doing the - cooking all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So she'd only get about three or four hours sleep a night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, about three or four hours sleep, and that - that was the good old days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever have washing brought in to do at home or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. They would have gone in the pawn shop if we had. Didn't matter who it belonged to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever have anybody else in to look after you children when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, you looked after yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did the older ones look after the younger ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes, you got 'em ready - you got 'em ready for school or the nursery. But 'em in the nursery for a penny a day. And then - and then call for 'em after you come out of school. See?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was St Paul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 s school a Roman Catholic school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no, no, just ordinary. I was married at - at St Paul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 s church, Harrow Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 In 1929. And I intend - shall I tell you something? I've got - a son - and two - two daughters. M
y son is a - City policeman, in the drug squad. He's six foot two and he weighs fourteen stone and his wife is - is nursing sister, in Wembley hospital. My daughter - she's married a chief surveyor of the Middlesex County Council. They live at Northwood. 
North - and my youngest daughter, she's married a - a manager of the Midland bank. There you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So they had a lot more chance then you ever had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, and now - and now - and the reason - and the reason I'm laid up now - is because I done two jo
bs - to keep 'em at college. They - they - all three of 'em - won scholarships at the same school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What was the other job you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Barman. In the West - in the West End. I flogged myself to death. And I - I finished - finished - finished up havi
ng two - two - two - two coronaries and - bronchitis and - and - and - and last - last year I had a - I had a - had a stroke. I was in - in this hospital for five and a half months with a stroke. Well that - that's how - that's how - that's how - that's h
ow my days was when I was a kid. Well you couldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did your mother have all the children at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Can you remember anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes, yes, go - go - go round and fetch the all woman that - that - that - the midwi
fe. And - and - and get her - get her a drop of gin, two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pennorth of gin on the way to keep her warm. And - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did the children help in any way or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh no, they - they - they - they did - they didn't - didn't do that in them days
. They sort of kept out of the way. The pubs was open 'til twelve o'clock at night. And if he - if he got tuppence - if he'd got tuppence in his pocket he'd go and have two - two half pints of beer and get out to the way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he go drinking quits a lot normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, well never had the money to go. My dad. He could drink, but he never had the - never had the money to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would your mother ever give you any money to buy sweets with or anything lie that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no. I - what - what - what
 - what sweets I - what sweets I - I done - done - done a job on a Saturday, outside a grocers, selling - selling biscuits outside a - outside a grocer - grocer's - shop, with a - with a - with a white apron on. But I gave more - more bloody biscuits away
 than I sold - to - to lads. Anyway the - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
In 1911 and '12 '13 and - and - got - got a shilling for that. Started nine in the - started nine in the morning and - and - and - and clearing eight o'clock at night. In the pouring rain in the winter. A shilling a day. Oh and your dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did any of the other brothers and sisters do anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, they done - they done - done some - they - girls kept - kept - kept - kept the house - you know, kept - kept the r
ooms clean, and the - the - the boys went out and - and one - one sold - penny indicators, you know, newspapers. And - I - I - I - I rode the - the - the chain horse to - to pull the - pull - pull - pull the carts up Harrow Road Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 A chain horse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. A chain -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Chain the horse to the carts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes, yes, you - you - you - you saved up two - two - two shillings you see, and then you hired the horse, and they give you a bag of grub, and for that two bob you earned what you like. See? You 
could earn perhaps five shillings on a Sunday morning. On Saturday. See? If you - if you liked to stop out. But of course - the Saturdays, it was a busy - busy day, it ain't like it is now. No - nobody works. You had the - you had the - you had the trams 
going up and down Harrow Road as well. The electric trams used to run - down - down Harrow Road then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What would you do on Sundays, would you go to Sunday school or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I was in the choir, I had to go and sing - sing in the choir four times a day. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How did you first get on to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well - they - they - I - I was picked out at school. I - I - I got - I was - I was - had me voice - sounded and they - they - they - got to go to - Sunday school and then to - to - to the Sunday sc
hool afternoon, then to - to dinner, then it was church - service in the - in the - in the morning and church service at night, that's how - that's how I got in to - to - to be at the top. Until - 'til I - 'til I - I punched this bloke on the nose and I g
ot the sack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were there any other boys like yourself in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
They was all - they was all from - they was all from - a choristers - college. But they was all - boys with Eton suits. But I - I - I was only - I was only loaned to them. See? Just to - just to sing the solos.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How long did you do this for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh two or three - about sixteen months I think, 'til - 'til - 'til me voice broke. And then I left - left that - left that - left that church choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was that St Pauls church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, 
this is Holy Trinity church - in - Bishops Road. Then - I left that and I - I got - got - got another church in a church choir, St Mary }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 Magdalene\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 , in Cirencester Street. Come - come - come down - from four - four pound thirteen a quarter to two pound thi
rteen a - two pound ten a quarter. It was good money in them days. And I had to - I'll tell you what, there's - there's - there's dozen - dozens of boys - that - could sing, you've heard that song - you've heard that record, Hear My Prayer have you? Every
 boy in our choir could sing as well as him. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Mario Lanza?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No, the - the - the - Robert - Robert Luff his name was. He - he's a - he's a fireman now. And - and - every - every boy in - in - in the choir has - has as good a voice as him although he was just lucky to be picked out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was he in the choir as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, he was in - he was in - he was in the - the - St James' - up in the City.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you know him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I didn't know him, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever go along to Sunday school before you went to join the choir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, we never went - he was after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What age were you when you started singing in the choir, about ten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, about - about - about ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you go to Sunday school before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you go to church before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
to Sunday - Sunday school perhaps in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did anybody else in your family sing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 The old - the old man was a good singer. Good - good bass singer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he ever sing in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, only when he was drunk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever have any musical instruments or anything like that in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no, not 'til - 'til - not 'til 1920, we - we bought a piano then, well we got some - got some furniture then. "cos I play - play 
- play - play the guitar now. Well not - not now 'cos I - I - I haven't got the strength you see, and - and I - I played - played the piano and the banjo. Not - not - not - not professionally but I can keep a party going. I play - I played at the night in
 - in - in pubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was there much music in pubs in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes. You had - people did - if you didn't have - if you didn't have a pub you never - you never got any trade. Because people - people in them days, that they - they used to go in th
e pub - and - they'd - they had - they had - and they had bars - they had little windows all round, that used to pen. Used to shut the windows so people - people shouldn't see who was behind there. They were frosted glass you see. So - if you - your guv'-
nor was in there talking see - somebody, and you was having half a pint - in another bar, you couldn't se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 e who - who he - who he was hob}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 nobbing with. Or if he'd - if he'd got a bird with him see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So it was all segregated up was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Could you go into any bar you wanted to though?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 If you had the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 There wasn't a sort of division amongst the bars?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. As long as you - long as you got the money to pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did women go into pubs very much in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, not a lot. They usually - they usually had a woman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
s bar - if they - they - they did. If they - they went out with their father - their hus - their old man they'd go in the saloon bar perhaps Saturday night. That's about the only time they went in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever go to anything like music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes, I went to the Met., yes. Metropolitan - Edgware Road. Went to the Kilburn Empire. You see - used to see - used to see - about six of us, we - we - we - get take us to - get tuppence - tuppence e
ach. And go down and - and - you'd all - one would rush up the stairs see - and - one'd - run up the stairs and you'd get to a seat - six of you, waiting there while the one got the tickets. Then you - you got three tickets see. For a shilling. Or perhaps
 there'd be nine of you going, when you get up the top, see, you - you - you used to work the attendant three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
pence and he would give you - give him the other - the tickets, see, where - where you're supposed to pay three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
pence for a ticket, you - you'd give him - give him the three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pence see, and he'd - he'd - he'd let you all in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So everybody was open to bribes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of things went on there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They never - never had no - never had no mikes. Good - good programmes the
y was, the old - the old - all the old times. Florrie Ford and - Chergwyn and all that - all the old - all the old timers. And - oh we had some real - real - real - real nights, sometimes you go to - go to - go to - go to the theatre - about three times a
 
week if you'd - you'd - you'd had a good day cab ducking. You know what cab ducking is? Well - in the - in the old days - you used to go down Paddington station - hang about on the plat - on the platform, and wait til the - the cabs are loaded up with the
 luggage, then - then you - then you'd sit on behind - and ride to where the cab stopped. See? And then - you - you'd help the - help - help the - help the driver unload - unpack - unpack the luggage and carry it in, he - he'd give you three}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pence. Yes. And you do - do that two or three times a night you - you'd had a good night. You'd have a fish supper and all for two}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 pence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you do this when you were still in school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. When - when you was in school - you did anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You had to use your wits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
You had to use your wits but - you had to think to yourself now what shall we do tonight to get a - to - to get a tanner? 'Cos if you didn't get - didn't get a tanner, you hadn't got a penny to put in the gas. \{BLANK\} Pudding, pease puddi
ng - pudding and faggots for your - your - for a penny pease - a pennorth of pease pudding and a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 penny faggot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When would this be, on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh - any day, any day in the week. All day long - they - they'd have 'em hot, pease pudding and - and - and - and - pigs trotters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would they be cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Cooked already in the window all steaming hot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So by and large you'd get your mother at Tussauds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, oh yes, used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Or get it out in the streets from the shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Get it around - around the streets. What do you - what you - what you couldn't - what you couldn't buy you pinched.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever get caught for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, I never got - caught. I was - I was - I very nearly did. I pinched a few bottles of beer for the c
oppers. The - the - when the coppers used to come round the streets, we - we used to put - a bottle of beer - we used to pinch these 'ere bottles of beer from the - from the off licence and put 'em down - down - down by the - the - the - the canal wall, u
p at Delamere Crescent, behind the trees there and - and we would stand there and see 'em come and drink 'em and then we'd go and collect the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did the police ever come down on you though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. They give you a clump round the ear'ole for lett
ing off fireworks or playing football, but - they was - they wasn't - they wasn't brutal. They kitck you - give you a kick up the arse and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Your mother never told you, if you're naughty I'll call a policeman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Well I - remember the time
 - we had the - the - the - bloke used to come round - sell - selling tar - tarry logs. On a donkey barrow. And - he used to - have - have what - in a bowl, about eight a time, nine logs in a bowl and - he'd take 'em downstairs to the old woman, fill her 
a
pron up. While he'd gone - while he'd gone down there we - we undo the traces of the donkey and as he come up the top of steps he day, go on old girl, and then away he went with - away'd go the donkey and up'd go the bloody lot. He run me all - he run me 
all the way - all the way - oh all the way from Harrow Road to Gloucester Terrace. Yes, with the whip. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where would you play in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where you play, you play in the Paddington recreation ground, or - in a mews. Or - or in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Never in the back yards or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, well they - they - too - too small, backyards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you ever go into neighbours houses to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Always frightened - always frightened you'd pinch something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - collect anything, what for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Like stamps or cigarett}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298  cards or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, well we used to play - we used to play - play - play - with cigarette cards. And gamble with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How would you gamble with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - you
'd have a - proper - proper pack of cards. You - you - you had a hand - handful of picture playing - playing cards and - you - you played banker. So many pictures cards on - on a number, then you cover it and if you won you won, if you lost you lost.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you play for money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well you - you - you - if you lost all your cards and you wanted to buy some - you - you had any money you buy your cards back. The bloke - the - the banker, he - he'd be making the money. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever go for many walks?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No. Took me all of my bloody time to walk - to walk from - from Paddington to Baker Street of a night to - to - to get the next day's grub. Then I - when I done that walk I was nearly sold out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You didn't have anything like a bicycle then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Only one I nicked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
You didn't get caught for that either? Did anyone besides your brothers and sisters and parents live where you stayed, did your mother have any lodgers or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It all - we all - mucked in together, you know what I
 mean. Where are you going? We - moved about in gangs. Gangs you know. But then - then - none - none of them got into any - trouble like they do now - they - they - drugs and - bloody - knocking people about and all that. You might pinch a bike for a day 
and - and leave it the - the - the next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have many relatives living near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh no. They was the same as us, hard up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did they often come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, on and off. If they wanted to borrow a shilling or we wanted to borrow a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You didn't have any sort of social evenings or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Nowhere to sleep, no - nowhere - nowhere to sit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did neighbours ever come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Your mother and father wouldn't get much time for going out themselves in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 She - was always at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would your father ever take you out on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No, never went out with him. Well I say I never went out with him - not - not 'til - 'til - 'til when the war came on, of 1918 - you know - I was old enough to go in the pub with him then. And pay for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would your father ever do any jobs around the house, mending or looking after the children or making fires, things like tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. He couldn't - he couldn't knock a nail in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would anybody do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, it - it'd all be - heat it up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What times of day would you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well you'd - you'd eat in the morning and - and - what we got, if there was anything left you had for dinner. And then - and then you'd
 have to wait 'til afterwards - mother came home for supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you eat straight away then when you came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 About eleven or twelve o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh I'd - it'd make me hour - to walk from Baker Street. And make - eight o'clock. Get home about a quarter past nine. Then go to bed.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What would you do for drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - have a - have a - a penny packet of cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Not coffee or tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, well always a penny packet of tea. You generally bought a penny packet of cocoa. Wouldn't have no - no sugar or milk in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 But you say you had meat most days of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, we had - what - that's what - what me mother nicked. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you ever buy food in the shops at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, the - well the - when she d
rew - when she drew her - when she drew - when she - when she drew her wages on the Friday see, she - she - she used to Saturday night get home at eleven o'clock well the - the markets was open 'til twelve o'clock Saturday night, and they}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 d go out and get the - get the - get the - they'd get the week's shopping. What there was to get. As far as the money'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So Saturday night would be the shopping night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you get in enough to last you the whole week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh no, blimey mine last Tuesday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would your mother ever eat with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh - no, she was a good cook she - she'd - she'd manage - she - she'd make a dinner out of nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When would she be home to make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you have anything different on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh well we - we had the - joint - joint - half a crown joint of meat. And - half a - half a crown bit of beef or - bit of salt beef you know, boiled. Bit of - sirloin of pork - or strips of pork. Made up in a stew, or a steak and kidney pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of cooker did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well and old - old gas cooker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you eat in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Slept in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have one table to eat off or how did you eat your meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh we - we just - just - just s
at down on one - one - one - one - one big square table and - ten chairs and sat - sat down there like in the back - in a barrack room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Have - have a laugh, have - what you - what you've been doing 
all day and - the old man - he'd - he'd say go to a pub and boys have to - I'd want to read. He'd - he'd go to the library and get a book and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he often get depressed with being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. He was glad when he went back in the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he ever take it out on you children when he was fed up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Knock - knock the daylights out of you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was he always like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 We just took it as - as - as it come you know, just - that was the way - just his way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was he very strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes. And we had - had a tuppeny pair of boots. Odd boots. He'd make you clean 'em - to go to school with the next morning. And they had to be cleaned. Under - Underneath as well as - unde
rneath the instep had to be cleaned. One - one - one - one lace up boot and one button up boot. For to go to school with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 If you ever got into trouble could you take your problems to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - he'd say, well - well what did you do? So and so, so and so, well - you got - you got - you got into trouble, you get out of it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you feel very close to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, she was all right, that was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was she someone you could take your troubles to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 If she had time to listen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did she show much affection for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How did your mother and father expect you to behave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well you - you - expected you to look after yourself 'til - 'til they - 'til they - 'til they come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you think you got the idea of how to live from one or the other or from both of them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well - my - my father - my grand - my - my grandparents - they - they - they - they were Gipsies. So you can see that - why we - we - it was born in us how to look after ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 On which side of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
On mother's side. See? Yes, my grandfather was a cattle dealer. He - he couldn't he couldn't add up - he couldn't add - he - he - he couldn't add three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 ha'pence together. No. And he'd tell you how much a horse was worth. Yes. And how - how much a sack of oranges are worth. Or how much a sack of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 po}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 tatoes are worth in the market.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were all her side of the family Gipsies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So I suppose they'd be travelling around the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh, mostly round Suffolk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did they ever come back down your way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Oh yes. I - I went - went and - I went to meet him at Liverpool Street once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were there ever any fairs or circuses round that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Wormwo
od Scrubs. Oh yes. Wormwood Scrubs and - Paddington Green. 'Course it's altered now, you was in - can't - you can't describe it now like it - used - you would do in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How often would fairs and circuses be round then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh I don't know abo
ut that, they come round - come round - Easter time, they - they come round - come round Whitsun time, holiday time - Bank Holiday. And then they'd go - they - they'd travel the - travel round the country - to the - to various fairs you know. Like they - 
they'd - they'd have Barnet Fair and they - they - they'd have another - another fair somewhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did these relatives of your mother's work at the fairs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. YES. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How did people look of Gipsies in those days, would they tolerate them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well they - they - they - you see, they - the gipsy today - he's - he's a different class of gipsy today. He's a scrap iron, scrap metal dealer. But the - the - the - before the war, the first world war in them days - you - you 
- you used to - to buy horses and buy donkeys and mules and - and - and make pegs, and - they was always making something. But you know - they - they cut bits of wood, and - and - and bind - bind them, you know, how - how a peg - and a how a - a peg is. W
ith the - with the - with a - with a bit of - enamel round it, see. Now they've got in - got in - got 'em with a clasp.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where would they stay, would they stay at the Scrubs and places like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no, they only - if you - if you - you - if you
 come there for a holiday you was allowed a - arrive Friday night you had to be off - Monday morning, by daylight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was this the gipsies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. The - the - the council, the - the - would have you off - have you - have you off the - off the - off t
he Scrubs - or off the parks, or - the - by - by - by - by the Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever go visiting them in Suffolk?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh we - yes, I - I - the - the old man, he - he bought - he bought a cottage - to - to finish his time in and - he bought -
 he bought - he bought a - he bought a cottage for sixty pound. Yes. Thatched cottage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where did he get the money from for that, from the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no, no, he - he - I - I'm talking about the old grandad. He - no, he - he - he got the money - he
 - he - he went to - a lady asking asked him could he get her a - a black - black legged donkey. Her grandchildren wanted a black nosed donkey. And - he - he was too - two - two days trying to get this black nosed donkey, and he couldn't get one. So he co
me along, he bought a donkey - and it was nearly black - and he got the black lead brushes, and he blacked - blacked - black lead - lead - leaded his nose and waited 'til it was dark and took - took it ro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 nd to the lady's house and sold it to her for fiftee
n pound. He only gave three pound for it. Yes. Of course it - and he - he - the donkey - and - 'til - 'til - 'til he got - got the - got the black - his nose properly - wt you know with drinking, he - it stayed on. Lovely place, Suffolk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever go there in the school holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I went to - I went to - to - to - to - to one poor law school holiday when I was a kid, I went to Ashridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Berkhamstead. And all that Ashridge - got an estate there, and - he - he - he let hi
s - let his estate out - a park - he set a camp up for a - for a - for a fortnight. Fortnight each school, so many schools. I think there was about - two months or two and a half months. As many as he could get in. Had - we had a fine deal down there. Gre
at old boy, old -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did you do down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh he - he - he'd take - he'd take - take you out shooting, or take - teach you to shoot, you know, show you how to shoot. And - you could eat all the fruit. Eat all the fruit there was laying on the
 ground. But you must - don't - don't pick nothing off the trees. Any - any windfalls you could have. You could send - you could send a s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12338065\charrsid16151298 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 ckful of windfalls home if you could get 'em home. But don't let him see you - catch - take one off the tree.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were your other brothers in the poor law school at the same time as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. All -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You all went out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Well you - you - my - you - you - my - my - my - my youngest brother, he - he - he was in a reformatory school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When did he go there, how old was he then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
He was only about eighteen. He wouldn't be - he played the wag too often. I - I - I - I hopped the wag too. I went fishing more than I went to school. I - I - yes, you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 This is the ordinary school, not the poor law school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No, the ordinary school. The old man'd take you to school. While he's talking to the headmaster away I'd nip. I'd be gone. I'd stop at - stop away - stop away a couple of - couple of nights or something and then - then - then turn - turn
 up at home, get a bloody good hiding, he'd take you back again. Get another hiding at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he want you to be at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Well you - you had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What would happen to your parents if you didn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 He - he'd - they'd s
ummons him. Yes. He'd get fourteen days if you - if you didn't go to school. Too true. Under the School Board for London. It wasn't the L.C.C. it was the School Board for London.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was it a board school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They all - all the schools - w
as S. - S.S. S.B.L. School Board for London. There was no comprehensive or - or - grammar schools or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. I - I left in standard four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Fourteen. I left - I - I left - I le
ft - left - left - left school - five minutes past four and I was at work in the pawn shop at five to five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 That was the first day you worked in the pawn shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. I - I only went in there - to try it, 'cos - 'cos they - they said you - you get
 a good tea. I had a good tea in there. And show - showed me where me bed was, under - we pulled the bed out from under the counter. You - you sleep under the counter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You were just selling things and taking things in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, yes, oh you - yes - y
ou - to - take - take the - the - the - the parcels in, pin 'em up. Stick the - stick - stick the ticket on 'em, whoever - whoever - you had - you had to pay - you had a pen with three nibs, see. The - the first nip - was the ticket for - for - for you, t
h
e second ticket was the pin - to pin on the goods. The third ticket was to go in the machine. So - at the end of the day - when you emptied the machine - see - that had to tally - with what you'd paid out. See? You never paid anything out - without a tick
et. If you only went across the - the - went across the - the road for a pint of milk - you had to write a ticket out, pint of milk. Penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How long did you stick that job for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Fifteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh I went - I went to - to - to - Wind - Wind - Windsor Court. In Mos - Moscow Road by Whiteleys. Block of flats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - porter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Can you remember how old your mother was when you were born and how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 She was fifty-eight when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When did she die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 She died in - yes, yes, about 1920 she died. And I - and I was twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 That would make her about thirty-eight wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So - thirty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 He died here when he was fifty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So he'd be about thirty-eight when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, yes. Fifty-seven. Twenty - he'd be - he was - 1919 he died. 1920. He died. And - and - I was twenty - twenty years old then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So he'd be about thirty-seven when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you know how old they were when they got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where did your father come from originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Marylebone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 He was local?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Local.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say your mother was from Suffolk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 She was a servant. She - she was in service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Is that where your father met her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes. During - during the - he was - he was a butcher - butcher's rounds-man. When he was a young man, of Gurney's in - in High Street, Marylebone. And she worked for a - for a firm - for a - lady and gentleman - in - Harley Street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 The Doctor's place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Doctor's place, yes. A very big - big - big - kept a very big family of servants they did. But I can't tell you their name but - she -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When you were young she was working at Madame Tussauds all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, when - when - when I was a - when I was old enough to - understand and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say when she was out at work you had to look after yourselves virtually?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Oh yes. You knew how to look after yourself all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did your father help with things like helping to dress or undress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 With baths or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. You get your ruddy - get yourself to - to - get yourself to bed and get yourself -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What time did you have to go to bed when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - whatever time we come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 There was no sort of strict bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Well there was no - there was no - there was no gas, I mean, we had to have oil lamps in them days
. Used to stop out 'til - 'til - 'til the - 'til it was too cold and wet to - to - you - or you wanted - there was nobody out to play - left to play with and you - you come in and got to bed. Had a couple of slices of bread and dripping if it - and a cup 
of cocoa for - for your supper. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You didn't wait up for your mother to come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh no. Oh no, never waited for her to come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What time would you have breakfast in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - I - I usually used to get up early - and 
go - go - go - with - with - with me other brothers and - and get the cheap bread and the cheap meat. At the - at the - the -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh get a - had to get up - get up about half past five. We'd be down the - down - down the bu
tchers at six. Line up. In the queue. With your tuppence or threepence for your cheap meat or cheap bread or whatever you'd gone - one'd go one place and one'd go somewhere else. And - when they was sold out if you was unlucky well you didn't - didn't get
 it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 That would be your breakfast would it, what you went to get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes. No, wouldn't have - that would be - that would be the - that would be - for - in case - in case - in case - in - in case - the grub was short from Madame Tussauds you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So what would you have for breakfast? What was left over from Madame Tussauds the night before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Or - or - or go without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So there wouldn't be a fixed breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no, you never - never had fixed breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 But you'd always come home from school for dinner would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well you'd come - come - come home - come home from school and - see what there was in the house - in - in - in the cupboard and - if there wasn't - was nothing there well just - you just have a slice of bre
ad and dripping or something like that and - and go back to school and - and wait 'til I - I come home from Madame Tussauds at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Ten people is quite a lot of mouths to feed really isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, it was a lot - a lot to feed. And then there was no dole you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Can you ever remember seeing your mother or father going without so that you could have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes. Yes. You - you used to have - used to have - boiled - baked - baked potatoes and - boiled rice sometimes for diner. Suet 
pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What time of day would that be, when you came back from Madame Tussauds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes, or - see, the pud - the pud - pud - put a - put a suet pudding on to boil - in the morning and it would be - be done by the time you come home dinner time for dinner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Who would look after it while it was cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well it would look after itself. If - if it - if it got burnt it got burnt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Who put it in, your mother or somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh the old man'd put it in or - one of us kids would. We 
had the on the - we had one of the - the - those big old iron saucepans. Fill - fill it up with water and it didn't - it would never boil - it would never boil dry. The - the only thing was that - that - that the - the fire - fire would go out. But - we h
ad - mind you we had those old - those old - kitchen ranges when once it got hot it was red hot for - for the day you know. And you could keep a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where would you get the cola from for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh you - oh you - you get the coal - off the coalman as a
 - shilling a hundredweight and - and - pay at the end of the week. Used to come round Sunday morning for the money. And - if you was lucky enough and went - went and paid the coalman the shilling for the - for the coal you'd get a penny off the coalman.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Because he didn't expect anybody to pay him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have set places for the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, you just sat down. Sat down to the - the - an old deal table and - sat where you liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Could you just get down from the table whenever you felt like it? Or did you have to ask permission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh you had - they - is it all right for me to get down? And go out to play or - oh you - you - if your mother wasn't there, well you - you wash the cups up or you wash the plates up, then you can go out to play. Sweep up. Sweep the floor up and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did your mother ever make her own foods like jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes. When the fruit was cheap in the summer. Oh yes. How - how long did that last. Make - you'd eat - eat a pound pot of jam in a day, the - a lot like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When would she find time to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did she ever make home made medicines or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, you - home made medicines you - all you - all you used to get is pennyworth of - of liquorice powder at 
the - the chemist. But we never had no - we had - we never had no - we never had no trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You never had illnesses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. The rougher you live the - the - the healthier you was. We had - we had a cold well just - we used to just - just get a pen
north of - of camphorated oil and rub your chest and - stick a bit of brown paper over it - over your chest and - and that was it. We didn't - wouldn't go round - go round to the doctor's for every - for - for every little ailment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You can't remember your mother or father ever being ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Only when they died and - not - no. The only time I do remember her being ill - was when she - she had pneumonia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When was that, how old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I was about - twelve or thirteen then. And she we
nt into the Paddington Infirmary. And - and we got notice to - to - to - to clear out because she knew she - she never got her wages from - from Madame - Madame Tussaud\rquote 
s then, you know, she wasn't at work and - the landlord, he - he let us run about four weeks and - told us we'd have to get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Even though she'd got pneumonia?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes. Anyway the - the old - the old man went - went to - I don't know whether he went to the pawn shop, and pawned something and - or pawned all he could get really. We had no sheets on the bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where would your mother be when she had pneumonia, you said they slept in the kitchen, your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 -Yes, well took - took - took - took - that's why they took her in the Paddington - local infirmary. They had
 the Parish doctor in you see, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would that be paid for on the poor law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You know, the poor law. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What was that infirmary like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh - it was proper - proper poor - poor - poor law Guardians place you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of things did that involve?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh the - straw mattresses and - general nursing like they - they gave - gave old people you know. Anyway she was in there - in there six weeks. She come out and she went - after a week or so she went back to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They kept the job open for her did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes. Oh yes, she was - a - a bloody good cook. She could cook. She could cook anything, French dishes. She - she's in - been in service. And kitchen maid. Right the way through, right - right to cook. And the - an
d the - the - the - the man - she worked for in Harley Street, he was a - he was a - millionaire. See? And - she could have gone to - she could have done - she could have gone - she could have gone to America with him. If she hadn't been married and had u
s kids. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did she ever regret that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh of course she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did she ever take it out on the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, never took it out on us. She always used to say - if it hadn't - if it hadn't have been for you kids I - I could have been so an
d so and so and so, so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well - all what - what - what - what sort of - what job you could get. I mean you - you - you had no schooling - practically - 'course I used to - 
I used to play the wag. And go fishing more than I went to school. And I - I left in standard four. And I left - left school on the - on the four o'clock Friday, and I was at work Friday at night at five o'clock at the pawn shop. And - you - you just - ju
st - got what job there was going. Riding a bike at a fishmongers or - at the butchers or - wine merchants. Errand boy on a bike. Or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have many part time jobs before you started full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well they was all part time jobs really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You mainly worked Saturday morning or Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Or in the evenings after school. Do - do a paper round or - but I - I - me mostly I'd - earn my few coppers cab ducking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What would your parents think about swearing or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh he was a bit - he was a bit strict on swearing. Although he could swear himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well I - she - she used to damn and blast a bit you know, but she - she wasn't - never used bad language.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
You never - never even - when - when - when - when we had - when we had company, if we did we was - never allowed in. Because there wasn't no - wasn't enough chairs to sit on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So would you stay out in the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Stay out in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 All ten of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about the very little ones, where would they go to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well they - they - well - younger than that they'd - they - they'd lay - lay 'em on the bed or - or put 'em to be
d and let 'em go to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What would happen if you did anything that your parents disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Bloody good hiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 From both of them or just one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh from the old man mostly. He was - he was a terror. Oh yes, he - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What other kind of things would you do wrong to get punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well he'd - he'd - he'd flay - he'd flay you with the belt or - knock you in the - if - if he was shaving and - and you was going - went - went - went by his elbow while he was shaving, or go
t - got near him while he was shaving you got a clump - clump round the ear for that, you didn't know what you was getting a clump for. He used to do - just - just - dodge - dodge by him you see. 'Cos he was so used to - so used to having - having a blood
y nigger - for - for about a penny a week when he was in India, cleaned his boots, shave him, and he used to treat - treat - treat us like that. He thought he was - he thought he was still in India.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you resent being hit all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Of course - of course we did. When - when - when - when we grew up -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You were telling me about when you were seventeen or eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, I - I squared up to him and told him - I'm going to have a show down with you now. We've had enough of your - being
 knock - knocked - knocked about just when you - thought fit or when you'd had a drink. And - he keep quietened down a bit then, 'cos my brother he was - he was older than me - when he see me, he - he shaped up to him and all. And - after - after that he 
w
as a - things was a bit quieter. Incidentally, when - when - when we was seventeen and sixteen - fifteen, we all began to earn a bit of money, things got a bit better at home you know. There was more to eat - and - mother still went to work see, she worke
d up 'til - 1919 when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you all stay at home all the time, did the sisters move out, go in to service or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no, they all - we all stay - all stayed at home. We moved - no, moved out - moved out that house, and got - got - 
got a - got a four - got a four roomed flat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh I suppose I would be - be about fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 That was about the first time you'd lived in four rooms was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 YES. Yes, oh - since the first time we had room to breathe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I suppose as you all got older it would be worse, all having to share one bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes. Well then - we - we got a - we - we - we - we bought some second hand furniture or - somebody died, you'd buy - half a dozen chairs, or a sofa. See a second ha
nd suite, get if for a couple - couple of quid. See? If any - anybody died - they left - left - left any old pictures or anything like that we'd - we'd - wee'd - we'd get 'em and - hang 'em up and make - make the place look something like. Ten -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say you can't remember how many times you moved in the first fifteen years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where was this place you moved to with the four rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Delamere - Delamere Crescent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you stay there 'til the end of the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, w
e we went then - we - we moved to - took a half a - half a house - half a house then in Ramley Road, by the Royal Oakbridge station. Did - did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have the whole house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Had - well they've pulled it down now. It was - it was backing on to W
estbourne Square in them days. Quite a posh neighbourhood for us to live in. If we hadn't - if we hadn't got a Sunday suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When would you have new clothes or best clothes to put on during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh when you - when you - when you - when you b
ought - bought - bought a new suit - you bought it on the Saturday - you bought it and you - you wore it on the Saturday or the Sunday. It'd go in the pawn shop on the Monday for the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did that happen all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Nearly everybody's suit went in the pawn shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would everybody get theirs on the same day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No, you'd - you'd get the - pawn the lot. And - and - and - you'd get - get thirty - thirty bob or two pound. 'Cos the - the rent went up then you see. And - from about four and si
xpence for two rooms - up to about - thirty shillings I suppose or thirty-five bob and - and the rent had to be paid, and - being the only way you could pay the rent was pawn the clothes. And of course, things did - things got better - better then, then t
he old man went back in the Army, he got his - got his Army allowance and - allowance for - for the children, that was under sixteen, see. My mother used to get - get the - get her allowance at the Post Office. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you do this when you were stil
l young, before you'd left school, did you have this routine of getting clothes and then pawning them on the Monday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, yes. We never had no sheets on the bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about the girls dresses and things like that, did that apply to those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They - they had to - they had to - to - to buy 'em on a barrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would they pawn those as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No, they wouldn't be fit enough to pawn. You wouldn't give nothing for 'em on the barrow, they - nobody would have 'em. But they - they were only tots. What - what they call dust \endash  dust-men\rquote 
s tots. And they could buy a - you'd buy three pennorth of - three - three pennorth of - women'd buy three pennorth of - stocking legs, see and then re - refoot 'em. See? Cut - cut - cut - cut three or four of
 the stocking legs up and make - make new feet of 'em. See? That's how they used to do it, yes. 'Cos they was only black stockings you see. And - where there was holes - used to - cut - cut - cut the - cut a shape of a foot out and - just saw it on the bo
ttom and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They used to last for a long time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Make 'em last a long time. You bought - bought - bought three \endash 
 three pennorth of stockings - on a barrow, you - you'd get half a sack - half a sackful for three pence. 'Cos they - 'cos - they were only totters theirselves. Getting a - getting a living on - on the barrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was there much sort of distinction between say people who did that and people like yourselves that had to keep moving house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well you all - you all - all living in th
e same - in the same predicament. You - you meet a neighbour of yours - where you living now Charlie? Oh - oh we're living down Sion now. Where are you living? Oh I - I'm living in Senior Street. Or - next time you see 'em, where - where you living now? O
h we - we - Oliver Mews or somewhere like that. Had another place. You get a shilling all day - cutting chaff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Turn - turning - hay - handle - big barrels of chaff - hay. And then to - cut it up for the - sell it - sell if for the - 
for the horses. And you - you work from eight in the morning 'til seven at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was that at certain time of the year or all the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 All the year round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I done that, yes. I - when I - when I - or if he wanted
 a boy or - he used to see - put a notice out, three boys wanted, four boys wanted. And you - then you - you'd - you'd - you'd cut the chaff by - by a oil lamp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When would you do this, what time, Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Saturdays. Or Friday night, work a - work a - while it was daylight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was anybody working on Sundays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes. Sunday, yes. All the butcher - shops was open - in the markets was open all - all the - up to the - two - two - two - two o'clock on a Sunday. Yes, you could get a 
- get your - you can get your joint of meat for Sunday dinner - up 'til - twelve o'clock Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about the religious people, didn't they try and stop it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh they take - they - they take no notice - take no notice of religious people;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Who were these religious people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well the Salvation Army and the - then the - the local priest and - and the old - the old girls that used to go to church, dish - dishing out the tracts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of people went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Only them - only them that wanted something. Went for what they could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of things do you think they wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh - mostly grub and - and - and old clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They used to get them on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, they went on a Sunday or - or - or perhaps a promise of a day's work. In the week. Go round cleaning somebody's flat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How would you get to know about that at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well the - the - you - you meet these - these - these old girls that stand in the porch at the church. Good morning Mr 
So and so, good morning Charlie so and so. Glad to see you at church this morning. How's your mother? Is your father at work? No. Well tell your mother to come round to me - on Wednesday or Thursday and I'll find her a day's work. Clean the bloody house o
ut or - for two bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How could she find time if she was working at Madame Tussaud\rquote s?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, I say, that's what - that's what they would say to other people see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of ladies were these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh they were - they - they had - they had the
ir - they had their - they had their carriage. A carriage and pair you know. Go - go - go down the - down the Mews and - for three pence you - you could clean - clean - clean the harness of the horse. See? While - while the old coach - while the old coach
 - coachman went up and had a pint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where did these people live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 In the Mews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was there much - you know people divide society into different groups in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Can you describe what the different groups would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well there - there - there were coachmen. And - cab drivers. And - father, he - he - he - you'd get a haircut for a penny. Penny - penny all off. With the clippers. And - you - oh you'd have all kinds of people. But - I - I always think - I
 always - always used to like - my job I - what job I - I liked best was cab ducking. When you - when you - when you cab ducking you had to be quick on your feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Otherwise you'd fall off wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Apart from that they'd - if you can't - if 
you couldn't run and catch the cab - you couldn't - couldn't sit on the cab when it started, you had to let it get a - ten or twelve yards away 'til the horse started trotting, then race after it. You - you - if you - if you couldn't get - if you couldn't
 run fast enough - you - you'd get some other kid beat you to it. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was it a sort of general rat race then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 General - general rat race. We had a - had a - had a - had a penny whistle. A pea - with a pea in it. If - anybody wanted a cab - you c
ould go out - go out and - and phone for a cab, you stood - stood on the corner of the street and whistled. One - one - one for a - one for a taxi, two - two for a - for a - two for a - for a four wheeler and - and - and three - three for a - a handsome c
ab. But that handsome cabs wasn't a very good paying job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How did you get jobs like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Hang around the - hang around the - the - the railway stations. And when you - when you got the - when you got to the place where the - where the - where th
e cab stopped and you unload - load - unloaded the luggage, you stood about a - a little while and - sorted out yourself and - caught - caught your breath and - all of a sudden you'd see somebody coming out want - want - want a cab, out of - out of a hous
e
. Want a - want a cab lady? Couple of blasts of the whistle. You see a - see a cab come round the corner. 'Cos they used to - cabs in them days - they used to stop at cab shelters. And all the - nearly all the roads and the main roads - they had green cab
 shelters. I dare say you've seen them about have you? I wonder - well I'll - I'll tell you where there's one now. There's one right - right outside - nearly outside the Albert Hall. See? Well they - used to be hundreds of them about like that. See?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I suppose there wasn't so much on the roads in those days was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No, well not only that, the old - the old - the old cab driver - he - he'd go in the cab shelter and have a cup of tea, and a yarn and - while his horse was having a feed. And then he
'd be out the cold, and then he - he'd listen for the whistles. See, and swallow his -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where were all these horses kept at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They had stables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did the cabmen have to look after them as well or was that somebody else's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, t
hey just had their own - just locked - locked up and they - they had one - they had one watchman used to just walk round and - see there was no fires or anything like that and - 'cos most of the cab - most of the cabbies lived - lived over the stables in 
two rooms. See? Or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You got on O.K. with these cabbies, they quite liked you helping them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes. 'Course - a lot of 'em were big - big - big fat - overgrown - balloted blokes - with beer, they couldn't - they couldn't carry the luggage up the stairs, see. So they was glad to give you \endash 
 three pence or a tanner even - to carry the trunks up the stairs. You see - the - footmen - of the house - he didn't consider it his - it was his job - to carry the luggage in. He'd carry it out. But he wouldn't 
carry it - visitors luggage in. Because he - he never got no tips. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So there was a market for everybody really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 There was a market - there was a market for everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did your other brothers help do this as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, if they - if they had - we all had our bits and pieces to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You didn't really have room to have lots of friends in or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, well there was too many people lived in the houses see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 But you didn't have many neighbours or friends coming round at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no, there were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Nobody else outside the house helped look after the family for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Christ no. They was all busy looking after theirselves. Or get - they had - their family was looking after theirself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever see much of your father's relations? Did they come round very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I never see 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was there much drunkenness and violence around the streets in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Policemen used - used - used to - used to - used to - about four - four o
r five coppers'd get a bloke down, two'd sit on him, or - there'd sit on him while - while - while - the other two - two went and got the stretcher. They had a - they had a - a cart, made like a stretcher. And they used to strap 'em on it. And they - they
'd push him up the road to this - they never had no - no police vans, you had - they had to walk to the station. If a bloke couldn't walk he had - had to put him on a stretcher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were there many policemen around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Oh yes. Well you can imagine 
- when I tell you - that Bishopsgate station - now - in the City - in The City in - is - is a square mile. The City is - the London Police Force is a square mile. There're over sixty policemen short at one station. They'd only got four stations in the Cit
y. And they're sixty policeman short in one - one station, so what - what - what must they be like in these - these - Metropolitan stations. They just haven't - haven't got the police - the men won't take the job on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was that so in your day as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, they could - blimey, once you got in the police you was made - made for life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It was a good job to look for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, well you - you - you - it was all - all - all - all the low brains if you understand me. All beef and no brains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How did they treat people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Pretty rough I tell you. Oh you - you - if you was taken - taken Saturday night you would - any trouble - you could hear 'em having - having - having a - having a hiding as you went by the station. And Carlton Bridge station, Ha
rrow Road there, Saturday night - or any night come to that, you go by there you could hear some - somebody hollering - was having a hiding. And you - you used to - Sunday morning - if we - we had the - had any coppers left, we used to - to go - go up the
 
Cut, up the canal, and - we'd have a gamble. Pitch and toss. You know. And the copper - copper used to - copper used to send his - send his - send his helmet round for - for a collection. See? And he done it once too often, he slung his bloody helmet in -
 in the - in the Cut.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did he do to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh - he had to get it out as best he could.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he chase you around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, we just jumped in the Cut and swum the other side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you go swimming in that place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes. Go swimming, rather. In Great Western Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was there a pond up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh the canal. Runs from Paddington Basin - runs right up to Birmingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Is that what the Great Western Road is called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Runs right - right through Green - Green - Greenford right - right the way through Berkhamstead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was that for barges and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Barges, yes, all day long, barges. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Wasn't it dangerous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. If you - if you got too far out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you know whether your parents had friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No. Couldn't afford to entertain them. Had a - we had to have - had - had a pint of stout, and bit of bread of and cheese and that was - that was a feed you know. But - as regards - looking - looking - for friends - never made any friends. Well 
you couldn't afford to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about next door neighbours, did you ever see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes - used to just - have a yarn with 'em over the garden wall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, had a back yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever grow vegetables and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Flagstones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You didn't have any livestock like chickens or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No. No. No, it's a real - it was real - real - real - real town. Actually - Hitler - he done a good job when he - when he - when he cleared this - thi
s - cleared the - cleared the slums out. He never finished a good job. Except for the fact that - the - the loss of life and all that. Incidentally I - I was in the A.R.P. for five years, I got relief - relieved - released from my job for the A.R.P. And -
 
I was - after two years or eighteen months or two years - I got - made - chief warden of this area. I was in charge of twenty-seven - thousand people lived in this - this area. I had sixty men under me. Until the war finished in 1945. Then I went back to 
me job. 'Cos all that service counted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It must have been a big responsibility?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
It was. I - I was in this - where they did this job outside this hospital, when the - when the - when the land mine went down. Fifty-seven people got killed. In Portob
ello Road there was another - two hundred and eighty-three people homeless, and nineteen killed. And - and the Great Western Road. And the - but the - the - the - the - the Co - the Co-op got hit and - block of houses there. And - 'cos I was - was - I was
 all - always on night duty you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I suppose it was completely different in the first world war, you wouldn't really know much about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, didn't know much. Well it was - it was - was - was - was - wasn't too far away. I mean - I did - did - 
did - did - did - did two - two - two years in the Royal - Medical Corps - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 In the first world war, you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. And that - that's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You'd be seventeen by then wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Of course I was - I was - old enough you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where did you go for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
I - I - to different - to different - different medical and - and military hospitals and - and on the ambulances meeting the wounded. Going out - going out to sea and meet the wounded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 This was from this country though, it wasn't abroad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 For - from this - from - from this country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 This was after you left the pawn shop was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. YES? After, yes. Oh yes, I had - I had - had - several jobs - after I left the pawn shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did you do after you left the pawn shop exactly, what kind of jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh I got a job as a porter in a - block of flats. And - I - smacked the - smacked the poor old - the - the - the head porter on the chin. Because he wanted - wanted - wanted - wanted me to - wanted me to 
stop 'til ten o'clock at night - for no over - time. I said I'd have the time off in - the next day. He said, oh no. Oh no you don't I said. Not time off the next day. Have the money in the - in the wage packet. That's what I'm interested in. Not the time
 off. Because if I had the time off - only - only meant - I'd have to go look - looking for - for some more work to fill the time in. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Didn't they have any trade unions or anything like that in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well they - they had trade unions. U
sed to be the union in the brickies. And - and the - the trades, but not - not - not unskilled trades.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So you couldn't get them to organize cases like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. No. No. But as I said - there was so many out of - so many out of work you - you dar
esn't put a foot wrong. But I took a chance hitting this bloke on the chin. I knew very well I'd get the sack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did you do after that? Didn't they get the police in or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. He just took it for granted. And - he - what did I do, I got a job - I got - got - I got a - got a job at Whiteley's then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 That's in Bayswater is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. A van boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Driving the van?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No - I'm behind - delivering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say you got four and six a week for the pawn shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I go
t - fifteen bob. Fifteen bob and - and me dinner. For - for the - for the porters job at the - at the - the - the - at the Windsor court.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What would you get for the van-boy job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh I - I got - got six - sixteen bob a week for that I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of hours did you have to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh all hours. No fix - no fixed hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about the porters job, what hours were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Seven o'clock in the morning - 'til eight o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have any half days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was that including Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, no, no. No half days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have anything like Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh I wasn't there long enough. Used to get some good tips though - off the - off the old - off the - the ladies that lived in the flats. You k
now just a couple of - couple of toms lived in the flats and - if they didn't want to see anybody or - Mr So and so calls this evening, tell - tell him I'm - tell - tell him I'm out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of ladies were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well on the streets. Yes. Lady 
- ladies of easy virtue. Oh yes. Perhaps they'd be in - in - enjoying themself with a - with a couple of blokes and - one of - one - one of their regulars'd call round. Is Miss So and so in? No, she's out. Oh all right, I - I'll leave my card, tell her I 
called. You get a shilling off of him. You get a shilling off her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were they all the people who lived in these flats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, they was all - yes, prostitutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What was the law like on things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well they - they used to shut their 
eyes to it with a - there you are - the - the girls, they didn't do it - did - didn't do it on the street, they had their regulars call at the flats see. It was in Moscow Road at the back of Whiteleys as a - as a matter of fact the - the - the - the - Win
dsor Court and Moscow Court belonged to Whiteleys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you find any distinction between people who were skilled craftsmen and people who were unskilled labourers in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well they - they ignored you you kno
w. They - if they met - met you out and they - they - as much as they do to pass the time of the day to you. If you - they - when - when - went - went out for a drink - Sunday dinnertime - they only went out Sunday dinnertime and they wouldn't - togged - 
t
ogged up in their best clothes and they went - went in the saloon bar. In the week you - you'd find them in the four ale bar. See? And they'd drink - they'd drink half a pint of bitter - on a Sunday. That it was - it - it was three hapence and a - penny -
 penny half a pint ale. In the - in the - in the saloon - in the - in the public bar. See, that's the - that's the kind of thing it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you remember anybody who was called a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Oh yes, there was - there was so
me ladies - visitors about, come and visit the poor you know. We all - real Christian ladies, they - they had real - done - done some real good work for people. There was - there was the - the - the - Christian Aid Society. They - they - they'd - they'd -
 
they'd - they'd - go round - to all - all the people - that - that got families - and - and they - they'd - get - get - get clothes from 'em, good - good clothes you know that to - that - what their - their - their children had grown out of. And they - th
ey - they - they'd sort these people out that had got big families and what - wanted clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have these ladies come round to you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, I - I had a Eton suit give me once. Yes. Yes. Yes, and they - they had - ruddy mortar board 
hat - with a tassel. And the - and the lads knocked - knocked - knocked it and kicked it about, and kicked it under the tramlines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I suppose you'd look the odd one out amongst all the rest in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. I didn't wear that suit long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were you ever taught to doff your hat to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Or show respect to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Never - never had a cap I don't think never wore one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes, well you never - you - you get to know people - that was - kindly towards you you know. That - that - that was feeling. I don't mean to say because - they give you a couple of coppers. But - if they met you out coming home from school - s
omewhere, they - they'd - say two or three of you coming home from school - would - would you boys like to come in to tea? It - send you down and get to the kitchen and tell the cook to give you a good tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of people were these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well t
hey - they were church - church people. All down Gloucester - down Gloucester Terrace and Westborune Terrace and all that. 'Course in them days then they had - they had property was - was - all - all had their carriage and pairs. And they had late dinner 
at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of people would own houses like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh the stockbrokers and - stockbrokers and - bank - bank clerks. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Schoolteachers didn't come in that class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What class would they come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
They'd come in the middle class. They were - they was having a job - to scrape a living together too in them days. Especially if they had a class like - like we had where you had to - we had to - to - to - to bring - bring a bag of - bag of rolls to s
chool, to give the kids some breakfast. 'Cos you never had no milk at school in them days. If you wanted a drink of water you had it out - had it out the fountain in the - in the playground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have just the one teacher or was there more than one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh no, only - only had the one teacher. Never - never changed classes like you do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You kept with the same person all the way through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes. That's why you didn't know nothing, you never knew nothing himself. He - he taught the sa
me old subject over and over again from the time he started 'til the time he retired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
I - either history or geography or - or - arithmetic or - so called arithmetic and - I didn't - I didn't know - I didn't know what decimals were - I couldn't do a decimal when I left school. I didn't know what they meant.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What was he like as a teacher though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 He was all right, he was. You had to do what you was told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was he very strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Very strict, yes. But - he was - he was good as they went you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did he treat everybody the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh no, he - if he wanted to cuff of the ear-hole you'd get it whether you - whether he liked you or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So he didn't have favourites or pick on people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of things did he - what did he think of things like punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh punctuality - you had to take your chance on time - what time you got there. You'd get a couple on the hand. For being late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What was his name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well the bloke - the b
loke I had, his name was Star - Starter. And - he was a bloody German as a matter - matter of fact. Spiteful bugger he was. He - he - he used to - come behind you and lift you up by the back of - by - by the - by the - by the hair. Pinch - pinch your ear,
 you know, and lift you up like that and - then as you - as you was sat down your seat so he - he'd - he'd - he'd - he'd give you one behind the ear-hole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 For no reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - for his reasons but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about things like manners did he expect you to be well behaved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, we had to sir him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did he think of tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well - I had a - in my - my family - he always had - a good - good name - 'cos my old man would make you clean - clean your boots - before you went to - b
efore you went to school, and - if - if you - your old jersey elbow was - was worn out he'd make - make my sisters darn it - of a night. See? So as we was tidy for school. Never had - never had a - never had best - never had a best suit. You wore the same
 suit all - all the - all the week, all the - all the week as - all day Sunday as you did all the week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When would you have a bath during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh Saturday night. Yes. Sit a tin - tin bath in front the fire, if - if there was a fire. Light t
he copper. And keep - keep dish - dishing - dishing the hot - dishing - dishing the hot water out of the - into the - out of the copper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Who would give you your bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well you do - you do - you do it yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Even when you were very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well if - if you weren't - wasn't too young. I mean after you was about six or seven you bathed yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Who would do it before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well the - the eldest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 He was eleven months older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, well - I had to - you bath - you bathed one another, that's how - that's how it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was it a mixed school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were they all in the same classroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, you had - you had - just had one - one to seven. Had six - six classrooms. Ab
out fifty - forty or fifty in a class - in a class. So you can guess the schoolteacher had a job on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 As you grew older you stayed with the same teacher all the way through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, moved up the next one. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So you didn't have the same teacher all the way through?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh not all the time, no. But once you went into his class, you stopped - stopped with him all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So you went through about four or five different grades?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes, and then the - the highest grade I got was - 
grade four. Standard four. Well that - that - the - the - the grade four would be equal to my - my grand - grandson's - education now and he's nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You didn't enjoy school really did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Hated the sight of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Why did you feel like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well I thought it was a waste of time. When I could be out earning money. When you're hungry you - you - you - you thought more about getting something to eat than you did about learning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you think you got anything out of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Nothin
g. They didn't teach me anything, they didn't know anything theirself. No. I learnt more after I left school than ever I did before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you think this was typical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Is it typical of the - of the schooldays? They do all the - all the - all the sch
ool boys - they either went on to the - on the Great Western Railway vans as van boys or - van boys or some sort of cycle boys or - until the war broke out and when they - when the war broke out then they joined the Army and the majority of them got kille
d and that got - got - got rid of 'em. So - that was one blessing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you remember whether there were any sort of gangs in the school you were at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Yes, there was the gangs all right. Fighting one another. All over nothing. Nothing really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was there anybody who got picked on at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh you - you - yes, you'd get a - get a bully. And - he'd get - get - get a bit - bloke a little bit soft or something and they - take the mickey out of him, well then you - well then you'd stand up 
for him you see. Then - then you - you'd be in a fight yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Can you remember anyone who was always on his own or left out of things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 For what reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well they - they'd got no guts. See? If I go - down Alfred Ro
ad, Paddington, they used to - used to - the road - the railway vans used to load up with - with bananas. Well used to get - get down there in groups and as they loaded the vans of bananas up so we used to knock off - knock a hand of bananas off. See? Say
 perhaps a dozen of us. And the bloke - bloke - bloke'd be - be - be a dozen hands of bananas short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was this during school time or after school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 After school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say you used to nip off to fish and things like that, did many children do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What means would they have of stopping you, did you just not turn up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Just - well just not turn up. You had the old School Board man - come - would come round on - the follow - following week and find out why you wasn't - wasn't a
t school. And then - then - the old man'd say - wasn't at school, what do you mean wasn't at school? And he - he - he was absent on Thursday and Friday. When you come home you - why didn't you go to school Thursday and Friday? Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What age were you when you first went to school, you say you were three and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Three and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Which school was it you went to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh you - you - your parents - your parents took you at three. 'Cos I'm next to the oldest, see. So when I grew up
 I had to take the youngsters. See, but my mother - my mother - mother had to take me to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of things would you do at the poor law school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh - wood - woodwork. They tried to teach you something. But your mind wasn't interested in
 it. They never - they - they'd never make a craftsman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Didn't they teach you English or maths or writing or reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Well just - just the ordinary - elementary - education you know, you - would - wouldn't have any maths or - anything like t
hat. All they was interested in was - soon as you was fifteen and a half they get you stuck in the Navy. That's -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 The Navy rather than the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Of course the - the - the Navy - they - they - they - they wanted boys at that age. See? When - whe
n - when - when you got a - when you got over fifteen and a half - see, and you heard a bit - about what the Navy was like, 'til you was fifteen and a - after you was fifteen and a half - you - you wouldn't join. See? And - once - you got away from the sc
h
ool - they didn't - didn't - didn't stand much chance of getting you in the Navy. But when they knew very well you - there's a gang of boys - due for leaving school - you had a medical and they - they painted a rosy picture up to you. See? Yes, it was - p
ress gang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What age was it you went from this school to the Board school, St Paul\rquote s school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Or did you alternate between the two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh I - well I went - I went - I went two or three times to different schools. Different poor - poor - poor law schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 But when you actually left school you were at St Paul\rquote s were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. YES? I - I left on a - I left on the Friday - at four o'clock and I was at the pawn shop working at five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did your other brothers ever go into the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, my eldest brother, he went in the Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What did he think of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, he - he stuck it right out for twenty-six years. As a matter of fact he done twenty-six years and - and come out and dropped dead.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever go on to do any evening classes or part time education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did any of your jobs have holidays with pay attached to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Only when I was at - only - only when I was at Debeham\rquote s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 But not before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. There was no - there was no such thing as paid holidays. And - and when - when I was - when - when I was at Debenham\rquote 
s - if you - and if you - if you a minute later - clocking on in the morning - you lost a day out your holiday. So if you was - a whole day for a minute. So if you was a day sho
rt, if you - you - rather than lose a day's holiday - you'd stop out and lose a day's pay. See? And of course come - come to lose to many of your day's holiday, you find you was - you - you'd got no holiday to come. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever go on holidays before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, I went to - I went to - I went to Scouts camps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Boy Scouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Church lads Brigade. And as matter of fact I was - I was - I was a leading - a leading side drummer in the Boy Scouts. And the bugle - and the bugle. YES? YES. And then the bugle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you enjoy the Scouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well - enjoyed as it - as far as it went you know, it was a bit - it - it was a - a giggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How did you get to join the Scouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well I just - just - just went round there and s
aid I wanted to join. They said - get a troupe up and then organize it, I said, I'll make one, all right, and bring some more round and - and - we got a - got - got a band up. At a - a shop - shop in Parade Street, I remember the name of it, Jakes, a musi
c
al stories, and bought - bought a bass drum, four kettle drums, six bugles, pair of cymbals. Eight flutes. Oh and - and - and the bloke that - that run it, he was - he was a - he was a good sing - good music teacher. Oh yes, he taught - taught you how to 
play the drums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 The Scouts had only just begun by then hadn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes. Only - oh yes. 'Course there was a lot of blokes - come out of the Army then so you - you used to - some like to show off what they know - what they knew you see. And - -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Whereabouts would you go on Scout holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I - I - I went to - I went to Dimchurch. Dimchurch. On the East Coast. On the South coast I mean. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was this in the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Just the summer. And week -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How long for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Who paid for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh you - you - you'd - you'd pay a penny a week and - and - and the - the church funds would pay the rest. That's half - half why we stopped in the Scouts, to go to camp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You went every year did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Were your other brothers or sisters in the Scouts or the Guides?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes, they was in Guides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 So you all went down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Not to the same camp. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever go on holiday with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Never went on holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say you used to go to Suffolk sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes, there was - see - see - see - see the old grandfather. And - when - when we got a bit older, he'd - he'd - he'd - he'd drive from Suffolk up to London with - with a - with a pony and cart. It'd t
ake him a couple of days to do it, and he'd take us back with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 All the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Stop down there for - a fortnight or three weeks perhaps during the summer holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 They'd look after you would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, feed you and - come home as fat as butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I suppose the country air was completely different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Well I nearly - nearly - nearly - nearly took up - nearly took up farm work Boy on the farm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you ever do things like hop picking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, I - no, I never w
ent - I never went hop picking. There's one thing that turned me off of that. I had a chance to go with a family - well - my brother and me and - had a chance to go to - hop picking and strawberry picking, and the old man said no. You go there you come ba
c
k lousy. 'Cos you had to - you had to - you had to - you had to sleep in pig sties. And on straw. See? Work in the fields all day. And - bed down of a night on straw in - in - in the pig sties. 'Course it's all - it's all different now, it's all machinery
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I've heard of whole families spending entire summers out hop picking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. Do - do six weeks out there. But usually the - hops used to start about - the end of August - and would finish - the hop picking'd finish the first - first week in - October. If it was a good - good - good year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Your father never went on anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
No. No, he - he wouldn't lower himself to do that. Oh no, we - yes, he was a - he was a smart - he was a smart - smart man you know, the old man was. Six foot he was - he was a Sergeant Major. And 'course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It must have been shattering for him to come out of the Army and not being able to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Get a job. He couldn't keep it going. 'Cos you see - things were really - from 19 - from 
1911 - 1910 - or 1909 to 1914 - when the war broke out things were rough. They was just as rough as what it was - in 1938, when they had four - three million unemployed in this country. 'Cos there wasn't the - there wasn't the big job - the big factories 
a
bout. They didn't - didn't went the big staff because you - they made you work so many hours. There was no such things as eight hours a day. Unless you was in a trade union. And it - only skilled people in the trade unions. And that is why they - that - t
hat's why they - they - they got away with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you think there was definitely a difference in interest between employers and workmen in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. You - you daresn't - you daresn't say as - any - anything to the - to - to - to - the 
employer then. You could tell him to go to hell now. And - and - and go down to the - Social Security and - and draw seven pound a week now and - and - tell him to go to hell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 There wouldn't be the Labour Exchange then would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well you woul
dn't - you wouldn't - you would - would - well you would - you wouldn't get his nose inside a Labour Exchange unless you was a - unless - unless - less - unless you was a - was a carpenter or a bricklayer or - for tradesmen see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 I thought they were for everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 It - yes, they was for everybody - who cared to go. But what was the good of going, there was nothing there for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You wouldn't get any money from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. You - you - you - you'd get - you'd get seven and sixpence - out of work pay. And that was only to pay your rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would your father get that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes, he'd get seven and six a week. Only for so many weeks. Then they say, oh you're - you're finished, you - find yourself a job now. We can't find you one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How many weeks would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh about six weeks. Then they'd - they'd - after another six weeks you'd go down again and try again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 When you first started work did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Even when you worked in the pawn shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Yes. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes, I got four - four shillings a week and - and slept under the counter. And I used to get - used to get paid twelve o'clock Saturday night - and I used to give her three shillings - Sunday. Keep a shilling a for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you go home on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, I'd go home Sundays. I'd go back to the pawn shop for dinner. But - I'd give her three shillings -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you still keep going to the church and choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Yes. But I didn't - didn't - didn't long - last long in the choir after I was fourteen. 'Cos me voice broke you see. Well I -

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have any choir outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes, day - day's outing here and there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 And went to Brighton. And Eastbourne. Go on the beaches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You seem to have got around a fair bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh yes. Anywhere where there was something going for nothing. It was the only way you lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you join any other clubs, you say you were in the Church Brigade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you have anything else at church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Well I - sang in the choir and - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you know if there was a temperance league?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, there was a temperance league, it wasn't much good though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 In what way, it didn't have much effect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Nobody took any notice of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was it a church or a chapel you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What kind of people went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Welsh people mostly. People - people I can't stand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Most people you knew went to church or not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 How did you get on with your first employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
The pawn shop. Very well. On the Saturday morning - after we closed the shop Friday night - he said to me after breakfast - get a bucket of water - a hose - and swill the area dow
n. I - so I swilled the area down and I found a shilling in a corner. I thought, now what shall I do, give this shilling up? Yes. I said to the guv'nor, I found this shilling in - in the corner. Did you, he said, now I - wonder how I - wonder how it got t
here? I said, somebody must have dropped it. Well he said, you'd better have that for your honesty. It was put down. Testing. So I - that was a good - do good - do good - good start to the day, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You say you had a rumpus with the other job, the porter job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you like the work in the pawn shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes. The only thing was there was no - no gas. You had oil lamp in on - and the smoke used to go - go up your nose. See, it was in the day - in the dark nights looking for the - for the parcels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Weren't the people who came in a bit sort of depressing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Oh I - half might pissed. They - they - they - Saturday - Saturday night they - they'd come in - boiling hot night Saturday night, some was eating fish and chips, some - some was
 eating tangerines, some - some was - had pease pudding and faggots. Cor blimey it was like Mother Kelly's doorstep in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What hours would you work on that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What hours? Seven in the morning 'til twelve at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, bar Thursday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You had Thursday off, what did you go on Thursday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Glad to get out and get a bit of fresh air. And when you closed - at twelve o'clock - on a Saturday night you wasn't done. You'd still got to put all the goods away. Any goods yo
u had lay - laying about in the warehouse. They had to be put - in - and stacked away because - in case of fire. See? Any - any goods laying about and - the - the - the - the firemen couldn't get at - blankets and all that kind of thing - you - you'd -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you think it was a fair wage that you got at the pawn shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Yes, I suppose they - four - four shillings a week. And say - ten or twelve bob for your grub. Half a crown for your bed. It was really - in those days it was - was fair.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about the other job, when you were a porter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 That - well that was fair because you - you got some tips. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you live at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. I had to start - had to start in - had to start at seven in the morning. And finish at eight o'clock
 at night. And the - he wanted me to stop one night 'til eleven o'clock at night. I said, what for? He said, well you'll get the time off another day. I said, what's the good of the time off? I said, I want a - I want - I want the money in the wage packet
, I don't want the time off, Well what am I going to do with the time off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you give the money from that job to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes. Oh yes. Oh for all - all - for about - bar - bar about three bob. 'Course I had a few tips you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What happened when you left school, did you still go round to Madame Tussaud\rquote s for the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh well of course - when - when - when - when - when - when - when Madame Tussaud\rquote 
s - job finished - the old - the old - the old man was in the Army then you see. The old man - and the old man was in the Army and - bit - things - she didn't have to work so hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was there anybody you called sir or master or madam in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh you called - called everybody sir and - who was anybody. You know - who you thought was anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about people like shopkeepers, what kind of group would they belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well they - some of them - some of them would give you - give you - give you tick. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Did you call them sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh, call them sir, ye
s. Oh I do - give us a couple of loaves of bread and - half a pound of margarine and - so and so and so an so. Pay you at the end of the week. See, and then you run a bill up. Then you - you run the bill up, pay the - pay - pay that week, then you - then 
you was all right for the next week. See, you work - you work - work the - the Madame Tussaud\rquote s grub - with - with the - with the shops you could get the tick at. And that's how you lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 The shopkeepers were quite good about it were they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Oh y
es. They - they - they'd drop - you a hit sometimes if the - if you - if you left it a week, you can't have this, we've got to keep open, we've got pay our bills. All right, we'll pay you next week. So you pay half next week and - half the week after. And
 that's how it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What about people like craftsmen, what kind of group do you think they belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would they be the same as teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well we didn't mix with them much. Not - not in our neighbourhood. We - we - we - we lived with the rough. When I was - when I was a kid.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Do you remember anyone being made to leave the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Made to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Made to leave the district for doing something wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Point is there was plenty of that. Yes, there was plenty of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Who would make them leave the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 The landlord for a start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 The landlord was the real villain of the piece was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 He was. You - you - you be out by - by - by Saturday. Else we'll come and sling you out. Well they did - they d
idn't - didn't wait - didn't - didn't wait for - for Saturday. They - they got a barrow and - and - and they moved out by moonlight. Do what - what they called - do a moonlight flit. There was - Humphrey'sa in Kensall Road - Humphrey's Kensall Road, he ha
d the big notice in his window, keep - keep moving. Humphrey's'll move you by moonlight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Can you remember anyone being made to leave by the people themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 For doing something the people disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No. Only robbing gas meters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 What would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Well they - they - they'd get chased out, you know. Life - life - life made - made unbearable.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 You can't remember anything like effigies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Or being made to leave by rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Who were the most important people around Paddington?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 
Well the - the - the - the doctor, the churchwarden - the tradesmen, the publican. He was - he was the - he was the - he was the most important man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Where you lived did all the poor people have the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Always the same standard of living. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Was there anything special about Christmas Day, did you do anything special on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Yes, go - go to church. Carol singing. Christmas Eve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you have any friends or neighbours in for Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13239045 WT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 No, we - had to feed 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2509290 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4005851\charrsid16151298 Would you have anything special to eat on Christmas Day?
